main event: On September 27, 1950, in San Jose, California, Frank Clark observed 10-15 objects traveling in a west to east straight line at an estimated altitude of 30,000 to 60,000 feet. The objects appeared to be shaped, and the observation took place during the day in the city.
interesting points: The sighting involved 10-15 unidentified objects traveling in a straight line, suggesting coordinated movement.
The estimated altitude of the objects was 30,000 to 60,000 feet, indicating a significant height and potential size of the objects.
The objects were described as shaped, adding to the mystery of their nature and origin.
Despite the observation taking place during the day in the city, no other witnesses to this unusual sighting were reported.
The data was considered as insufficient, with no follow-up information requested, leaving the sighting unexplained.
sighted object: 10-15 unidentified objects in a straight line
